[
    {
        "content": "<p>I often find myself in a situation like the following and this is my goto way to solve it. However, it takes more mental effort than I feel like should be required and so am wondering if there is an easier way:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">PartialOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b_lt_a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">False</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">elim</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">lt_self_iff_false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">gt_trans</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b_lt_a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_b</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491357077,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1735613463
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>personally I would just do <code>(a_lt_b.not_lt b_lt_a).elim</code></p>",
        "id": 491357314,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1735613666
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could also do <code>(lt_asymm a_lt_b b_lt_a).elim</code></p>",
        "id": 491357452,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Diamond",
        "timestamp": 1735613820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Those are both a fair bit simpler, thank you!</p>",
        "id": 491357843,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1735614128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=absurd#doc\">docs#absurd</a> is also good for such situations</p>",
        "id": 491358660,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1735614912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>exact absurd a_lt_b b_lt_a.not_lt</code>. or even <code>simp [b_lt_a.not_lt] at a_lt_b</code> for more complex situations</p>",
        "id": 491358780,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1735615036
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>After using <code>absurd</code> the goal can be closed by the output of <code>exact?</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">PartialOrder</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b_lt_a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">absurd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a_lt_b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `exact?` gives the following:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_lt_of_gt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b_lt_a</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491359802,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Qinchuan",
        "timestamp": 1735615952
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also replace <code>False.elim</code> by <code>cases False</code> if you want</p>",
        "id": 492018146,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1736129018
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>All great suggestions, thanks for the help. It’s super useful seeing all the different perspectives.</p>",
